Punargentus monticolens (
Butler, 1881
)
(
Hipparchia
) comb. nov.

subSubSection.paragraph:
Distribution . Found mainly in Bío Bío and Auraucania Provinces in Chile and in western Neuquén Province, Argentina , but can be found as far north as northern Mendoza Province, Argentina , east to the Paraná Delta just north of the city of Buenos Aires, Argentina , and south to northeastern Aisén Province, Chile , and to central Santa Cruz Province, Argentina , along the western border. Flies from November to February at nearly sea level to 3300m (
Fig. 29
).
